  <tr><td colspan="3" bgcolor="#183049">D'oh!  One more thing!  This is an incredibly handy spell.  Basically it stops the mob from regaining HP (or at least slows it down) for six full minutes *and* does 5 damage!  Combine this with a no-mana cost and it's a very useful spell.  The biggest downside is that Verant just about tripled the casting time.  I know the regular is 1 second, this one is around 3.  Pretty frustrating.  I mean, it's not like you can chain-nuke someone into submission, it only does 5 damage and by the level that you will probably be able to get it (providing that there isn't some huge Friendly-Newbie-Helping-Druids guild party in Steamfont at the time...) 5 damage will be next to worthless.  ALSO... (man I'm long-winded today 8) I'd say 10 is about the right level, perhaps 8-10.  The brittle skeletons are about the same as regular skellies that also roam the valley, but seem to have more than their fair share of HPs.  Better be good at timing those spells between hits ;)<br><br></td></tr>
